}} The '1991â92 season' was Colchester United's second consecutive season in the
fifth tier of English football. The season ended in success with Colchester
achieving promotion on the final day of the season, resulting in a return to the
Football League at their second attempt. They also won the FA Trophy after
beating Witton Albion 3-1 at Wembley Stadium.
